From Andi Beyer Subject Re Freedom In writes Dear Beyer It is never wise to confuse freedom of speech with freedom of racism and violent It is unfortunate that many fail to understand this crucial In fact if a speach was not offensive to some its protection under Freedom of speach laws would be It is speach that some find questionable that must be protected be it religiously blasphemous or inherently It is only through civilized discourse and not scare tactics that one can enlighten those that one perceives to be That is the idea behind freedom of What you find offensive might be perceived as truth by some and what they might find offensive might be your It is only through free exchange of ideas and insults as the case seems to be with this channel that one can change another's erring is why Jefferson said that here we are not afraid to tolerate error so long as reason is left to combat it